NAME
       cat - concatenate files to standard output

SYNOPSIS
       cat [FILE ...]

DESCRIPTION
       Reads each FILE in order and writes its contents to standard
       output. If no FILE is given, reads from standard input. The
       special filename '-' also denotes standard input.

EXAMPLES
       cat /etc/motd
       cat a b > c

SEE ALSO
       head(1), tail(1), tee(1)
